    "created_at": "2016-06-07T07:56:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-07T07:56:28Z",
    "body": "After looking into this issue for more, I'm closing this as won't fix.\n\nOn Windows and Linux, it is very common for borders to not have resize handle, for example the border of the close button:\n\n<img width=\"190\" alt=\"screen shot 2016-06-07 at 4 38 56 pm\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/639601/15849596/57d675c4-2cce-11e6-862e-f4e5ef313df0.png\">\n\nIf we force showing resize handle for all borders the behavior would actually not be expected.\n\nSo for users don't want to hide the resize handle, they should avoid marking the areas near the border as draggable.\n"
